# Writer Coordination

- Multiple writer subagents are allowed only when their writable scopes are explicitly disjoint before launch.
- Do not run write-capable subagents in background mode. If multiple writers are needed, launch them together in the same turn and wait for completion.
- Shared files stay parent-owned unless one worker is explicitly assigned as the sole owner. This includes `src/app.module.ts`, `src/main.ts`, `src/shared/**`, `prisma/schema.prisma`, route or permission regi stries, shared docs/contracts, and cross-module tests.
- Every writer handoff must list owned directories/files, forbidden shared files, and the validation commands expected for that scope.
- When parallel writers were active, the parent orchestrator must re-read the latest file content before applying any shared-file edit or merge.
- If overlapping changes appear and can be attributed to active child writers, reconcile by reading the latest content and merging on top of it instead of stopping immediately.
- Only stop and ask the user when the source may be a real user edit, ownership is ambiguous, or the overlap crosses a frozen boundary that was not approved.
